<DOC><DOCNO> AP890526-0046 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-26-89 0638EST</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--MotherRaped     05-26 0149</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Mother Raped,0153</SECOND><HEAD>Man Who Raped Mother Gets 16 Years in Jail</HEAD><DATELINE>COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man who raped his mother whenshe wouldn't give him money for cocaine was sentenced to 16 yearsin prison.   The 55-year-old woman left the court sobbing after Judge JamesFranklin issued the sentence Thursday. Her 30-year-old son wassilent.   The Colorado Springs woman said in an interview earlier thatcocaine had turned her son from an energetic, hard-workingindividual into a robber and rapist. He supported his $180-a-dayhabit by stealing things from her house, she said.   On Sept. 6, she gave her son $22 but he demanded more. When sherefused he raped her twice, the woman said.   The man pleaded guilty to first-degree sexual assault inexchange for dismissal of an incest charge.   The names of the mother and child were withheld to protect thewoman's identity. </TEXT></DOC>